{"/service/ndnp/arhi/batch_arhi_huskerdu_ver01/data/sn89051168/00393343254/1908032701/0703.xml":{"full_text":"A Remarkable\nLetter\nWe have received this somewhat\nremarkable communication with a re\nquest to publish.\u2014The Editor\nNew York City has for some time\npast established stations where those\ntoo poor to get Anti-Toxin might be\nprovided free of charge. The use of\nAnti-Toxin as a remedy for the ter\nrible scourge of diphtheria has been\nquite general, and the expense attend\ning its use has been so great, includ\ning the cost of making the bacterio\nlogical examination in order to deter\nmine if or not the patient has diph\ntheria, that New York among other\ncities has done her best to provide\nfor her poor who become stricken\nwith the dreaded malady. Part of the\ncost attending the use of Anti-Toxin\narises from the necessity of proving\nto a certainty that the sufferer really\nhas a case of diphtheria, as a great\nmany able physicians maintain that\nunless the patient has diphtheria that\nthe administering of Anti-Toxin is\nhighly dangerous.\nI have known whole cities and\ntowns living in dread of an epidemic\nof diphtheria. In Minnesota, Wiscon\nsin and Michigan a great many of the\nhospitals use Muco-Solvent. In view\nof the fact that any mother can buy\nMuco-Solvent without a prescription\nand administer it safely at the first\nfeverish indication or apparently\ntrifling cold or sore throat, the fact\nof the doctors in those hospitals using\nit, the drug is little short of remark\nable.\nWhere Muco-lSolvent is introduced\ninto a community stricken with diph\ntheria or croup or any of the maladies\nattacking the mucous membranes the\nmortality is reduced within forty\neight hours to zero.\nAny mother who has Muco-Solvent.\nin the house can rest easy as to the\nsafety of her family, for when Muco\nSolvent is administered deaths occur\nrarely from diphtheria or croup. In\nshort, the remarkable statement is\nmade by an officer connected with the\ngovernment bacteriological depart\nment that Muco-Solvent destroys the\ndiphtheria germs absolutely in from\n35 to 30 minutes, and does not af\nfect. in the slightest the human tis\nsues, being entirely safe to take,\neither internally, as a gargle or\nsprayed. Children have been saved\nfrom death by that dreaded disease,\ncroup, after being pronounced past\nrecovery by competent and able phy\nsicians. Once knowing the wonderful\nproperties of Muco-Solvent, as great\na discovery in its way as radium or\ntelegraphy or electricity, any mother\nwho fails to keep it in the house at\nall times is, in our opinion, commit\nting an act closely allied to criminal- j\nity. MeCammon Son have the cour- j\nage of their conviction, and without\nfear or favor guarantee every word j\nof file above as a matter of philan- i\nthropy. The supply at present is lim- I\nited. but doubtless in a short time it\ncan be bad at ail druggists.\nGRIFFIN TO\nMEET BARRY\n__ i\n\u25a0Waukegan. 111.. March 26.\u2014Hank\n\u2019Griffin, the colored boxer of Racine,\nWis., and Dave Harry, of Chicago, are\ncarded for the main bout at a show to\nhe pulled off tonight before the Cubs\nAthletic Club. The men will fight at\ncatch weights. Griffin was formerly a\nsparring partner of .Tack Johnson.\nPansy j\n(iiriger Ale i\nThe \u201cQuality\"\u2019\nGinger Ale\nThe main superiority of PANSY\nGINCfHR ALE o?er any other\nis in its superior quality, hut its\nitnaqualed flavor\u2014its whole- j\nsomeness\u2014all contribute to its\npre-eminence.\nAsk your grocer for PANSY\nBRAND and if you are offered\na \u2018\u2018just-as-'good\u201d keep your\nhand on your pocketbook.\n\nManufactured and\nBottled by\nOZARK FRUIT CO.\n1E1PHIS, TENN.\nFOR BILLIARD\nCHAMPIONSHIP\n.New York, March 26.\u2014Little Willie\nHoppe, the cue phenomenon, will at\ntempt to regain the prestige he lost\nby being defeated for the 18.1 cham\npionship by \"Wizard\" Schaefer, in bis\nmatch for the IS.2 championship to\nmorrow night. Hoppe has been prac\nticing strenuously for the contest and\nhis opponent, (Jeorge Sutton, the pres\nent holder of the title, will probably\nhave to play the game of his life to\nhold the emblem. The contest be\ntween lloppe and Sutton will take\n,pace tomorrow night in Madison\nSquare Garden concert hall and will\nbe witnessed by a large .assemblage of\nbilliard enthusiasts.\nTomorrow\u2019s battle of cues will be\none of the most important since the\nifirst international contest in 1873 at\nthree-ball caroms. This tournament\nwas won by Gamier. It was in this\nyear that \u201cJake\u2019\u2019 Schaefer made his\npublic debut at Indianapolis in a\nmatch with .Parker A. Byers, \u201cthe wiz\nard,\u201d winning by a score of 300 to 183.\nGeorge Slosson\u2019s first public match\nwas in 1S70, he being beaten by B.\nFrank Dennison. Slossom and Schaef\ner, lirst met on October 5, 1873, SIos\nson winning, 500 to 321. For thirty\nfive years the pair have had annual\nduels, and \u2018Schaefer is today\u2019 the 181\nchampion.\nMaurice Vignaux, the French cham\npion, came to America in 1874 and\nwon the first three-ball championship\nof America.\nSchaefer\u2019s first public match in the\nEast was in Washington, D. C., in\n1876. In 1870 he won the second cham\npionship of the world, defeating Slos\nson, Sexton, Daly, Gamier, Gallagher, 1\nRiulolphe and Helzer.\nThe balk line game was first intro\nduced in 1S83, being at six inch to\nstart with. Schaefer won the first\ntournament under these rules. In 1SS4\n(lie game was changed to IS.2, but this\nwas just as easy for the experts, and\nin 1885 tlie first 11.2 tournament was j\nwon by Slosson in New Y\u2019ork\nThe 3S.l and IS.2 style of game j\ndates back to 1895, and ft was in this\nyear that Sutton, the present 18.2\nchampion, won his first tournament,\nwhich was at 14.2. The first IS.2\ntournament was held in the spring\nof 1896 in New York, and in May of\nthe same year the first 1S.1 tourna- j\nmment was held in Chicago.\nGeorge Slosson was the first claim-\npion at the 18.1 game, winning the\ntitle in Madison \u2018Square Garden in\n1S97. There was no championship\nmatch until 1903, which was won by j\nSchaefer, who recently forfeited his\ntitle after defeating Willie lloppe.\nThe first world\u2019 schampionship at\n18.1 was played in Paris in 1904, Yig-\nnaux defeating Sutton.\nAbout this time Willie lloppe be-\ncame prominent, by winning the cham\npionship of \u201cthe young masters\u201d in\nParis, and two years later he chal-\nlenged Vignaux for the championship, j\nwinning the title by 500 to 323. Hoppe\nsuccessfully defended the title against i\nSlosson and 'Schaefer, but. forfeited it j\nto Sutton when he went to Amsterdam\na little more than a year ago, and\nsince then the latter has been beaten\nby Schaefer.\nThe IS.2 championship series start\ned in 1903 in Paris, Vignaux defeating\nSutton. The Frenchman\u2019s term its\nchampion expired in 1905, and the fol\nlowing year the second world's cham\npionship tournament was held in New\nYork 'City. 'Phis brought out some\nyoungsters, notably Hoppe, Cutler and\nOra Morningstar. Slosson won the\ntournament in the spring, but was j\nbeaten by Sutton in the fall and now\nSutton must defend his title against j\nyoung Hoppe.\nYANKEE HORSES\nIN ENGLAND\nLondon March 2t>.\u2014Two horses i\nfrom Foxhall P. Keene's stables will j\nuphold the racing honors of America\nin the running of the English Grand\nNational tomorrow- The race this j\nyear is worth $15,000 along with a j\nvaluable trophy, and is the greatest j\nearly event on the British turf. The\nanimals which will carry the Keene\ncolors at the Alntree track are\nProphet HI. and Chorus, a chestnut\nmare.\nAmong the entries. King Edward\nheads the list with Flaxinan. Eremon,\nthe sensational winner of last year, is\nan absentee, so that the mishap to\nStanley Howard's horse is more seri\nous than was at first thought. Among\nthe veteran brigade are Drumeree,\nwho was victorious in 1902; Asceti's\nSilver, the hero of 1901 and holder of\nthe record for the course of 9 minutes\ntit 2-5 seconds, and Kirkland, the vic\ntor of 1905. Other old ones are Tom\nWest. Red Lad. Ranunculus and Ra-\nvenscliffe.\nLadies' don't let other affairs keep\nyou from the mass meeting at Mer\nrill institute. We all want a clean\ncity, and there\u2019s strength in numbers.\nJust like mother used to make;\nWhen she would chance to bake\nWith Success flour. 3-16-tt\nKNICKERBOCKER\nBANK RE OPENS\nNew York, 'March 2G.\u2014Marking an\nother decided step toward the return\nof prosperity to the metropolis, the\nKnickerbocker Trust Company, which\nclosed its doors last October, was re-1\nopened for business at noon today.\nThe bank has assets of over $50,000.\n000, with liabilities slightly less, and\nthere is every likelihood that it will\nbe able to pay all of tlie 20,Odd depos\nitors in full.\nThe reopening of the Knickerbocker\nTrust Company, in accordance with\nplans for its rehabilitation, prepared\nafter four months\u2019 labor by a commit\ntee of depositors, released to the cont\nmunt.v assets aggregating $46,370,620.\n\u201cThe reopening of the Knickerbock\ner Trust Commpany,\" declared Janies\nHussell Seely of the counsel for the\ndepositors\u2019 committee, \"will have a\nstimulating effect not only upon the\nlocal financial situation, but upon ev\nery financial center on the globe. I:\nis the best thing that has happened\nsince the panic.\u201d\nJustice Clarke, in dismissing the\ntemporary receivers of the suspended\ntrust company and signing the re\nsumption order, spoke in commenda\ntory vein of the work of the deposi\ntors\u2019 committee, counsel and others\nwho had labored so assiduously in\nworking out the rehabilitation plau.\nUnder the terms of this plan the de\npositors of the Knickerbocker Trust\nCompany will not receive their de\nposits in full when the trust company\nopens its doors, but will receive 10\nper cent, today if they want it and the\nremaining portions of the deposits can\nbe withdrawn at intervals covering a\nperiod of about two and one-half\nyears.\nY. M. C. A. CONVENTION\nA\u2014\nFrederick, Md.. March 26\u2014Dele\ngates from Maryland, Deleware, West\nVirginia and the District of Columbia\narc here in large numbers today for\nthe opening of the interstate conven\ntion of the Young Men\u2019s Christian As-\nsocial ions. The meetings will be held\nlaily until next Sunday. Large dele- j\ngations are here from Washington,\nBaltimore, Wilmington and other\neities. United States Senator Robert\n/.VI. LaFollette, of Wisconsin, will de\nliver an address on \"The Nation\u2019s\nGreatest Need,\" and many other prom\ninent laymmen and clergymen will\nspeak. Headquarters for the dele\ngates have been established in the new\n$6,'),000 Y. .VI. C. A. building in this\ncity.\nA word to the wise Is enough\u2014\nuse Success flour. 3-15-tt\nALABAMA BASE\nBALL SEASON\nTuscoloosa, Ala., .March 26.\u2014With\nthe first of a series of three games\nagainst the Owenton College nine this\nafternoon, the University of Alabama\nbaseball season will be opened. The\nschedule provides for series of games\nwith Univerity of Mississippi, Univer\nsity of Georgia, University of Texas,\nAlabama A. and M., Georgia Tech..\nCentral of Kentucky and Louisiana\nState University.\nTAF TO SPEAK\nIN PHILADELPHIA\nPhiladelphia, March 26.\u2014\u2018Secretary\nWilliam H- Taft, presidential candi\ndate, will be the guest of honor and\nprincipal speaker at the annual din\nner of the Yale Alumni Association of\nPhiladelphia, to be held at the Belle\nvue-Stratford, Saturday. President\nArthur T. Hadley, of Yale, will also\nbe present and respond to a toast.\nTENNESSEE\nBANKERS MEEt\nMemphis, Tenn., March 20.\u2014For the\nfirst time since 1S93, Memphis will be\nthe host of the Tennessee Bankers\u2019\nAsociation. The convention will ex\ntend through two days and many\nfinancial subjects of importance to\nTennessee and the South will de dis\ncussed.\nThe essence of wheat, is what to\neat. Success flour is the miller\u2019s\nmaster production. 3-15-tf\nGET HAPPY\n\n\nCome on\u2014Make life worth the living-\u2014Get happy clothes made\nfor you\u2014not dummy clothes.\nSee the new jungle shades and soft, pretty browns.\nP. RUTSTE5N SON\nLEADING TAILORS\n01,1> PHONE D60. 119 MAIN STKEET\nmm 5 fies\nSEE US FOR\nMissouri Mules\nInspect our Stock\nbefore buying.\nStables, Barraque and*Olive\"Sts\n-^rvAf\u00abyr ts^r\nPINE BLUFF,:ARK.\nSSMmBtsL'\nHORSES AND MULES\nALL KINDS AND SIZES.\nAlways a large number to select from\nWe sell REAL, MULES and HORSES\nOur reputation for square dealing is\nten years old.\nSEE rs BEFORE BUYING.\nCHAS. PRUDEN CO.\n2045, 208 and 210 East Barraque Street,\nIN PNEUMONIA TIME USE\nPNEUMO EMOLLIENT\nIts failure to give quick relief is unknown in cases of Pneumonia.\nFor LaGrippe, Bronchitis, Pleurisy, Sore Throat. Hoarseness, Pneu\nmonia, Cold and Lung Troubles it will prove\nTHE REMEDY\nThat has no known equal. It neither Burns nor Blisters and has\na pleasant odor.\nManufactured hy\nWEIL CHEMICAL CO.\nPINE BLUFF, ARK.\nFor sale by Druggists everywhere, or sent postpaid on receipt of\n$1.00\n\nel tame\nI\nALCOHOL 3 PER CENT.\nA\\\u00a3ge(ablePrepantfionforAs\nsiraila l ing the FoodamIRegula\nring die S toraachs anilBowelsof\nInfants /Children\nPromotes DigpstionJChterfiil\nness and Rest-Containsneittar\nOpium.Morphine nor Mineral.\nNor Narcotic.\nfinipt tfoMkSMitimm\nfleadtui Seed~\nJit. Jam*\nJhxMftM:\nmteSeid\nHim Sad\niSUa*\nAperfect Remedy forConsfipa\ntion. Sour Stomach.Diarrnoea\nWorms .Convulsions .Feverish-\nness and LOSS OF SLEEP.;\nTac Simile Signature oT\nNEW* YORK._\nAtb months old\njj Doses-35CENTS\nO^nranteed. under the\nExact Copy of Wrapper.\nFor Infants and Childrj\nThe Kind You Have\nAlways Bought\nBears the\nSignature\nof\nIn\nUse\nFor Over\nThirty Years\nCASTOBU\nTHE CENTAUR COMPANY, Nt W YOR\u00ab CITY.\nI\nti\nI 1\nw\ni\nE are no;; ready to connect up\nGas along the route o